[Main]
Name=CU_cursorState
Type=Variable
Subtype=ROM Call
Header Files=system.h
Definition=signed short CU_cursorState;
MinAMS=2.00
See Also=CU_restore, CU_start, CU_stop

[ROM Call]
Index=$503

[Description]
Contains the current cursor state (on or off).

[Explanation]
CU_cursorState contains <A HREF="$$LINK(alloc.h/Bool)">TRUE</A> if the cursor is on, otherwise it contains <A HREF="$$LINK(alloc.h/Bool)">FALSE</A>.
<BR>
If it is on, this does not mean that it is displayed, but that it is allowed to be displayed.

